
Syntax: f_ind [<range>] "text"   
        l_ocate [<range>] "text"
        f_ind [<range>] ["text"] A=login
        l_ocate [<range>] ["text"] A=login

Description: This will show all lines of responses in items in the specified
   range which contain the specified string of text.   If no range 
   is specified, "all" is assumed.  In the latter forms, all responses
   by the login specified will be found, and the first line of each
   displayed, unless a text string is also specified.  If both an
   author and text are given as arguments, all lines of responses by
   the author specified which contain the specified text will be shown.

See also: range
